<section class="page-hero page-hero--compact">
  <div class="eyebrow">MISSION · ARCHITECTURE · ACCOUNTABILITY</div>
  <h1>Built to show<br><span>its work.</span></h1>
  <p class="lede">Forge Atlas is not a fake network of autonomous agents. It is a maintainable static interface with an optional same-origin Worker layer, honest demos, and local-first tools.</p>
</section>

<section class="section section--flush-top" id="truth-layer">
  <div class="section-heading">
    <div><div class="eyebrow">01 · OPERATING MODEL</div><h2>Clear boundaries.<br><span>Useful results.</span></h2></div>
    <p>The interface remains useful without a backend. When providers are configured, their exact runtime identity appears beside the result.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="card-grid">
    <article class="card"><span class="card__index">STATIC CORE</span><h3>Fast everywhere</h3><p>Pre-rendered semantic HTML, one global stylesheet, page-specific assets, no third-party font dependency, and no blocking intro gate.</p></article>
    <article class="card"><span class="card__index">WORKER EDGE</span><h3>Secrets stay server-side</h3><p>Provider credentials, URL fetching, input validation, fail-closed rate limiting, and response normalization live in the Worker—not browser JavaScript.</p></article>
    <article class="card"><span class="card__index">TRUTH LAYER</span><h3>Status comes from evidence</h3><p>Reachable is not the same as healthy. Optional is not the same as live. Editorial simulations remain labeled.</p></article>
  </div>
</section>

