<section class="section">
  <div class="prose">
    <div class="eyebrow">03 · DESIGN PRINCIPLES</div>
    <h2>What the platform optimizes for</h2>
    <p><strong>Truth before theater.</strong> The visual identity can be cinematic without presenting scripts as current provider output.</p>
    <p><strong>Operator control.</strong> Prompts are submitted deliberately. Profiles can be exported. No hidden production controls are exposed in public UI.</p>
    <p><strong>Portable architecture.</strong> The static build can be hosted anywhere; the Worker is isolated behind a documented API contract.</p>
    <p><strong>Safe failure.</strong> Provider outages produce a visible unavailable state. Curated fallbacks only appear after the visitor chooses them.</p>
    <h2>Version policy</h2>
    <p>The release displayed in headers, footers, health responses, documentation, and generated files comes from <code>config/platform.js</code>. Stale “two minutes ago” telemetry is not generated.</p>
  </div>
</section>
